    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-08-08T22:19:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-08-08T22:19:00-05:00" n="770"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d770">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.516/8–949: Telegram</note>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clark</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-08-09T11:19:00+08:00"
                            >August 9, 1949—11:19 a. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 9—11:19 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cantel 888.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>Department, Taipei note. 200,000 ounces is second gold airlift ordered by Central
                    Government from New York account within few weeks (previous 100,000 ounces
                    Canton) leaving balance gold custody account about 40,000 ounces. Significant
                    that destination is Taipei and urgency emphasized by Central Bank for need this
                    gold meet “current expenses”.</p>
                <p>Sent Department Cantel 888, repeated Taipei 98.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clark</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
